On 31 July 2012 at 12:36, David Ibarra G?mez wrote:
| Hi Peter,
|
|         I'm looking at MPI examples, thank you for the advice.
|
| But If It's possible to use several instances with MPI. I think It should be possible with OpenMP.

You missed the subtle point that Open MPI spawns multiple _processes_ (which are independent) where Open MP spawns multiple _threads_ (which are not).

One works, the other doesn't.

